    "claim": "`poolCheckpoint()` credits users with CVX based on `computeClaimableConvex(claimableCRV)` before any claim occurs. That helper applies one cliff rate to the entire CRV amount, even though actual Convex minting is cliff-dependent and can decrease as a large claim crosses cliff boundaries or as total supply changes before execution. The accounting can therefore book more CVX than the pool will ever receive.",
